entries.meaning: Having eight lobes or leaves. [from 19th c.]
examples: Then there was the cool air as I entered the front hall of Number Twelve Šporkova, the metal box for the electrics built into the wall beside the entrance with its lightning symbol, the octofoil mosaic flower in shades of dove grey and snow white  […]

entries.meaning: (heraldry) A stylized flower or leaf with eight lobes; a double quatrefoil.
